comments.text:
Confirmed on Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:15.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/15.0

I try to explain why this bug should be fixed as soon as possible. It is useful to known from which server you are downloading from, in situation where:
a) the server limits your simultaneous downloads;
b) you don't want to saturate the band for that server;
c) you want to check if you are downloading from the nearest one;
d) [security] checking if you have been redirected to an untrusted server.

